<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" NumberSubstitution.CultureSource="User" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Verdana" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:space="preserve">Exif Macro in </Run><Run FontFamily="Verdana" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:lang="en-ca">Watermark Text</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333">Select the watermark text box below to enable the dropdown and button. Move cursor to your desired position in watermark text, select the macro you need and click "Insert Exif Tag" to include the macro in your current cursor location.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333" xml:space="preserve">The macro basically is just a tag surrounded by "[[" and "]]" delimiters, feel free to use normal text editing mode to move them  around or delete it.</Run></Paragraph><Paragraph><Run FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="13.3333333333333">You can add as many Exif macros as you need.</Run></Paragraph></FlowDocument>